::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' Curved wood must be bent again to reach straightness, and finding truth from exaggerations and lies takes knack. When the real is fake, the fake is also real, and you need to toss a coin to hear my spiel.
::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' I am Xiyan, a humble storyteller at the Sleepless Earl. If you'd like to listen to a few novel-length tales, you might have to wait here for a while.
::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' ...Then again, though there is still time for the story sessions, if you were to sip some tea and listen to a few tunes, it wouldn't be a complete waste of time, would it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You are a storyteller, but also involved with running the tea house here?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502104005-->
:::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' {{MC|m=Good sir|f=Madam}}, don't talk like that. If the tea house has business, then more patrons will come to drink tea. With many patrons, I then can make friends and earn a little money for myself.
:::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' Besides, the tea at the Sleepless Earl isn't too shabby. If you'd like some recommendations, I'd say order a pot of Hunter Maofeng tea. Satisfaction guaranteed.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Great. I was just about to order some tea.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502104008-->
:::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' Then you've come to the right place. The Sleepless Earl is the premier tea spot aboard the Xianzhou Luofu. Don't let the innkeeper's young age fool you. Her research on how to simmer tea leaves is unrivaled.
:::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' If you wouldn't mind my humble opinion, order a pot of Hunter Maofeng tea. Satisfaction guaranteed.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502104010-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502104010-->
::'''Mr. Xiyan:''' Some guests are tea aficionados, and often pontificate about all kinds of expert tea lore at the Sleepless Earl. I'm not a smart man, but I have memorized some facts and can show them off. Would you be interested?
